label.value: nonkeratinized epithelial cell of inferior part of anal canal

value.value: A nonkeratinized cell epithleial cell of the inferior part of the anal canal.

label.value: keratinized epithelial cell of the anal canal

value.value: An epithelial cell of the anal canal that is keratinized. This cell type is found towards the lower, rectal end of the anal canal.

A respiratory stem cell found at the junction of the terminal (conductive) bronchiole and the respiratory bronchiole. This cell types gives rise to alveolar cell types and club cells in response to lung injury. This cell type expresses markers Scgb1a1 and Sftpc.

An amniotic stem cell is a mesenchymalstem cell extracted from amniotic fluid. Amniotic stem cells are able to differentiate into various tissue type such as skin, cartilage, cardiac tissue, nerves, muscle, and bone

definition.value: Not clear to me if amniotic stem cell is a different cell type from amnion mesenchymal stem cells. They are treated as distinct in the literature as isolations methods are different, so I will keep them as separate terms for now.

value.value: An epithelial fate stem cell derived form the amnion membrane.

label.value: epithelial cell of esophageal gland proper

value.value: An epithelial cell of the esophageal gland proper.

label.value: epithelial cell of esophageal cardiac gland

value.value: An epithelial cell of the esophageal cardiac gland that occurs both in the proximal and distal esophagus, within the lamina propia.

label.value: nonkeratinized cell of stratum corneum of esophageal epithelium

value.value: An epithelial cell of stratum corneum of esophageal epithelium that lacks keratin.

label.value: endo-epithelial cell of tympanic part of viscerocranial mucosa

value.value: An endothelial cell of viscerocranial mucosa that is part of the tympanic region of the viscerocranial mucosa.

label.value: endo-epithelial cell of pharyngotympanic part of viscerocranial mucosa

value.value: An endocranial viscerocranial mucosa cell that is part of viscerocranial mucosa.

label.value: endothelial cell of venous sinus of spleen
Endothelial cell of venous sinus of red pulp of spleen
Endothelial cell of venous sinusoid of spleen

value.value: An endothelial cell that is part of the venous sinus of spleen. This endothelial cell has an elongated, spindle-shaped, flattened morphology that is parallel to long axis of sinus. This cell type rests on a basement membrane interrupted by numerous narrow slits.

label.value: endothelial cell of high endothelial venule
Endothelial cell of postcapillary venule of lymph node

value.value: A venule endothelial cell that is cubodial, expresses leukocyte-specific receptors, and allows for passage of lymphocytes into bloodstream.

definition.value: Markers expressed on HEV include: MAdCAM-1,PNAd (sulfated and glycosylated molecules, i.e. GlyCAM-1, CD34, endomucin, nepmucin), ICAM-1, ICAM-2,Fuc-TVII, beta 3GlcNAcT-3, GlcNAc6ST2,CCL21, CCL19, CXCL13, CXCL12, Autotaxin, DARC, angiomodulin, LRHG.

value.value: A endothelial cell of the venule that is squamous shaped. This is in contrast to the cubodial shape of high endothelial venule cells.

label.value: epithelial cell of stratum corneum of esophageal epithelium

value.value: An epithelial cell of stratum corneum of esophageal epithelium.

label.value: epithelial cell of stratum spinosum of esophageal epithelium

value.value: An epithelial cell of stratum spinosum of esophageal epithelium.
A glandular epithelial cell of the endometrium.
A glandular epithelial cell of the esophagus.

label.value: glandular cell of the large intestine

value.value: A glandular epithelial cell of the large intestine.
A glandular epithelial cell that is part of the stomach.

label.value: luminal cell of acinus of lactiferous gland

value.value: A luminal epithelial cell of mammary gland located in acinus of structure.

definition.value: Consider if synonymous with mammary alveolar cell CL:0002325. Some use this term to refer to the non-lactating cell type that gives rise to the lactating cell type.

label.value: luminal cell of lactiferous terminal ductal lobular unit

value.value: A luminal cell of terminal ducts, i.e.e the terminal branch of a lactiferous duct which alveolar cells drain into.
A luminal epithelial cell of the lactiferous duct. This cuboidal epithelial cell expresses keratin-18 and is estrogen-receptor alpha positive.
A myocardial endocrine cell that is part of the atrium.
A stem cell that can give rise to multiple cell types (i.e. smooth muscle, endothelial) in the developing heart.

definition.value: Discrepancy in develops from origins prevents me from making the assertion that cardioblasts give rise to all instances of cardiocytes as we state cardiac muscle cells develop from cardiac myoblast, which in turn develop from muscle stem cell.

value.value: A fibrocyte of the cochlea that has specialized structural and molecular adaptions.
An otic fibrocyte that underlies the spiral prominence and is part of a mesenchymal gap junction network that regulates ionic homeostasis of the endolymph.
An otic fibrocyte that resides above the stria vasularis and is part of a mesenchymal gap junction network that regulates ionic homeostasis of the endolymph.
An otic fibrocyte that is lateral to the basilar membrane and anchoris it to the lateral wall.
An otic fibrocyte that lines the otic capsule.
An otic fibrocyte that underlies the stria vascularis and is part of a mesenchymal gap junction network that regulates ionic homeostasis of the endolymph.
An endothelial stalk cell is a specialized endothelial cell that follows behind the tip cell of an angiogenic sprout.
A multi-fate stem cell that can give rise to different retinal cell types including rod and cone cells.
A skeletal muscle cell that is part of the tongue.
A S. pombe mating type determined by the mat1-Mc and mat1-Mi on the mat1 locus.
A S. pombe cell type determined by mat1-Pc and mat1-Pi on the mat1 locus.
A neuroblast derived from a neural crest cell.
A regulatory T cell that has not encountered antigen.

definition.value: This cell type has been described as CD45RA-negative, but this doesn't fit with our current definition of naive T cell.

value.value: A CD4-positive, CD25-positive alpha-beta regulatory T cell that has encountered antigen.

definition.value: Cell has been described as being CD45RA-positive in human, but this doesn't fit with our current definition memory T cell.

value.value: A lymphocyte found in adipose tissue that lacks lineage markers of other lymphocytes but is capable of mediating TH2 cytokine responses. This cell type is found in fat associated lymphoid clusters, proliferates in response to IL2 and produce large amounts of TH2 cytokines such as IL5, IL6 and IL13
A PP cell found in intestine.

definition.value: A retinal ganglion cell that has dendrites stratified in two layers of the inner-plexiform layer.

value.value: A retinal ganglion cell that has a small dendritic field and a medium dendritic arbor with post sympatic terminals in sublaminar layer S3.
A mono-stratified retinal ganglion cell that has a small dendritic field and a sparse dendritic arbor with post sympatic terminals in sublaminar layer S3.

A bistratified retinal ganglion cell that has a small dendritic field with sparse density that terminates at the intersection of the S4-S5 sublaminar level, and a second dendrite field that is medium in size and degree of arborization that terminates in sublaminar layer S2.

definition.value: is_a bistratified retinal ganglion cell S4-S5 dendrite field having (small dendritic field, sparse density) and second dendrite field having (medium, meduim)
A mono-stratified retinal ganglion cell that has a small dendritic field and dense dendritic arbor.

value.value: A G4 retinal ganglion cell that has post sympatic terminals in sublaminar layers S3 and S4 and is depolarized by illumination of its receptive field center.

definition.value: A G4 retinal ganglion cell that has post sympatic terminals in sublaminar layers S2 and S3 and is depolarized by decreased illumination of their receptive field center

value.value: A mono-stratified retinal ganglion cell that has a medium dendritic field and a medium dendritic arbor with post sympatic terminals in sublaminar layer S2.
A mono-stratified retinal ganglion cell that has a medium dendritic field and a sparse dendritic arbor with post sympatic terminals in sublaminar layer S4 and S5.
